Federal prosecutors exceptionally seek the death penalty for suspected terrorist attack in New York City
Federal prosecutors in New York are looking for capital punishment for Sayfullo Saipov, the suspect of the terrorist attack in New York City that killed eight people, an exceptional punishment that has not been executed in the state for a federal crime since 1953.
