Several weeks after the attack, a large federal jury presented Saipov with a charge of 22 charges that included eight murder charges with the help of organized crime, which usually use federal prosecutors in these cases, and a charge of violence and destruction of motorized vehicles.
The attack required "substantial planning and premeditation," according to the prosecutors, who described how Saipov carried it out as "atroz, cruel and depraved."
